1
00:00:05,435 --> 00:00:12,761
cw: (mutual) confinement, arguably justified drug use, intimacy as a coping mechanism for PTSD. Please proceed with caution and avoid reading if these topics may be distressing, triggering, or uncomfortable for you.

2
00:00:12,761 --> 00:00:19,715
This date contains STRONG REFERENCES to Season 1, Chapter 25 and [Not Planned On] R&S. If you haven’t read them yet, I highly recommend doing so first for a more immersive emotional experience™.

3
00:00:19,715 --> 00:00:26,670
Another date that I recommend to read before reading are: Embrace Date (Shower Karma SSR), Tidying Date (Childhood Solo SSR) because these two dates also delves on his ptsd and ‘possessiveness’. You can either find it on my tumblr or search on youtube as the date is already localized in EN server!

4
00:00:28,966 --> 00:00:32,612
I feel like I'm going to die.

5
00:00:32,612 --> 00:00:35,211
The world is spinning, and the sudden sense of weightlessness crushes my heart as if it could burst at any moment.

6
00:00:35,211 --> 00:00:38,790
I cross my hands and press my head tightly against the back of the seat. The oxygen mask on my face inflates and deflates with my rapid breathing, and white mist engulfs the breathing bag in the blink of an eye.

7
00:00:38,790 --> 00:00:42,909
Captain: Our plane has encountered an unexpected situation during the flight...

8
00:00:42,909 --> 00:00:45,711
Captain: Please fasten your seatbelts... Do not panic...

9
00:00:45,711 --> 00:00:48,682
The hoarse announcements, deafening roars, and helpless cries collide chaotically, pulling me into a state of bewildered despair.

10
00:00:48,682 --> 00:00:55,332
…Am I going to die here?

11
00:00:55,332 --> 00:00:58,202
A figure appears before my eyes, and amidst the violent turbulence, his face seems to grow increasingly blurred.

12
00:00:58,202 --> 00:01:00,633
Several pieces of luggage crash from above, hitting my shoulders and completely shattering all my thoughts.

13
00:01:00,633 --> 00:01:03,941
The scenery outside the porthole speeds past in reverse, with raging flames and thick black smoke seemingly burning wildly in my eyes, leaving only silent pleas and prayers.

14
00:01:03,941 --> 00:01:05,292
??: Buddha, please protect us...

15
00:01:05,292 --> 00:01:06,777
??: No...

16
00:01:06,777 --> 00:01:13,664
As an invisible huge wall slams into me, the air in my lungs feels as if it’s being forcibly squeezed out. Amid the piercing roar, my consciousness is gradually torn and pulled away.

17
00:01:13,664 --> 00:01:15,015
MC: Lucien…

18
00:01:16,095 --> 00:01:19,640
Deep beneath the surface, bright light illuminates the rough concrete walls and rows of metal instruments. Several blonde researchers move back and forth through the somewhat modest laboratory.

19
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:22,442
Lucien stands in front of the second-floor platform, calmly looking down without revealing any emotion.

20
00:01:22,442 --> 00:01:24,974
A foreign gentleman stands beside him, his profound green eyes gleaming sharply as he raises his palm.

21
00:01:24,974 --> 00:01:27,742
??: Doctor X, I didn’t expect our formal meeting to occur at such a chaotic moment.

22
00:01:27,742 --> 00:01:30,949
Lucien: Indeed, it is a bit unexpected.

23
00:01:30,949 --> 00:01:37,060
Lucien: However, to smoothly avoid the turmoil in such a short time and maintain such a well-equipped research environment...

24
00:01:37,060 --> 00:01:39,356
Lucien pauses, his narrow eyes showing a faint smile devoid of warmth.

25
00:01:39,356 --> 00:01:48,505
Lucien: It seems that aside from research, Professor Holden also holds considerable authority in other areas.

26
00:01:48,505 --> 00:01:50,767
Holden: Professor Lucien, if you want to stay in such a volatile place, you must be well-prepared.

27
00:01:50,767 --> 00:01:52,488
Holden: Risks and rewards always go hand in hand.

28
00:01:52,488 --> 00:02:01,773
Lucien: In that case, I think we can further accelerate the pace of the experiment to minimize the risk.

29
00:02:01,773 --> 00:02:09,943
Lucien: I don’t intend to let meaningless disruptions become the key turning points of the past several months I’ve worked on.

30
00:02:09,943 --> 00:02:12,880
A silent tension faintly brews. Feeling a slight sense of pressure, Holden raises an eyebrow and places one hand on the railing in front of him.

31
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:14,703
Holden: I’m just as eager as you are, Professor.

32
00:02:14,703 --> 00:02:16,424
Holden: But in these chaotic times, there are always accidents.*

33
00:02:16,424 --> 00:02:20,577
As if in response to his words, a barely perceptible hum comes from above. The ceiling trembles slightly, shedding a shower of fine gravel.

34
00:02:20,577 --> 00:02:23,041
But everyone present seems accustomed to it, continuing their work unfazed.

35
00:02:23,041 --> 00:02:24,966
Lucien also looks up without surprise, gazing into the distance.

36
00:02:24,966 --> 00:02:29,861
Lucien: Accidents are meant to be controlled and enjoyed.

37
00:02:29,861 --> 00:02:39,753
Lucien: Chaos will ultimately become the catalyst for new discoveries, and that’s why I chose to work with you in the first place.

38
00:02:39,753 --> 00:02:45,424
As he speaks, he turns and walks away. Just as he steps into the open elevator, a voice calls out with a laugh from behind.

39
00:02:45,424 --> 00:02:47,619
Holden: With Professor Lucien joining us, I suppose we should indeed be more confident.

40
00:02:47,619 --> 00:02:50,083
Lucien doesn’t respond. With a loud rumble, the old elevator doors slowly closed behind him.

41
00:02:50,083 --> 00:02:53,054
The sound of metal grinding outside the elevator continues to roar persistently, like the distant echoes of endless artillery fire.

42
00:02:54,236 --> 00:02:58,760
The fading afternoon sunlight streams in from outside as the elevator doors open.

43
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:00,920
Three days have passed since the meeting with Professor Holden.

44
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:03,655
The lab operates around the clock, almost pushing time to its limit, but the results are still not ideal.

45
00:03:03,655 --> 00:03:05,411
Just as Lucien expected.

46
00:03:06,592 --> 00:03:09,023
He extends his fingertip, verifying one fingerprint scan after another, before stepping out of the unassuming old factory.

47
00:03:09,023 --> 00:03:12,365
The scent of gunpowder constantly assaults his nostrils. Scattered armed personnel stand guard in front of barbed wire fences among the crumbling ruins on both sides.

48
00:03:12,365 --> 00:03:15,302
Lucien walks steadfastly through this land where turmoil is the norm. Only when he passes a corner does he finally stop and take out his phone.

49
00:03:15,302 --> 00:03:17,969
The signal bars silently returned to full. While waiting, he looks up at the sky not far away.

50
00:03:17,969 --> 00:03:22,257
A vast expanse of dark clouds churns and burns fiercely. Soon, the phone in his palm vibrates.

51
00:03:22,257 --> 00:03:24,620
Lucien opens the message box and sees a text from the girl six hours ago, informing him of her boarding.

52
00:03:24,620 --> 00:03:27,692
She is on a private plane back with several film industry executives. He instinctively calculates her estimated arrival time in Loveland City—

53
00:03:27,692 --> 00:03:30,089
She will land in about four hours. His expression softens unconsciously, and a hint of a smile appears at the corner of his lips.

54
00:03:30,089 --> 00:03:32,891
Lucien's Message: Miss Producer, you must be tired from your business trip. Thinking about how you'll be home soon… I feel a little lonely too.

55
00:03:32,891 --> 00:03:34,984
Lucien's Message: Looks like I want to wrap up my work early so I can get home sooner to see you.

56
00:03:34,984 --> 00:03:37,348
Pressing the send button, he hears an increasingly loud whirring sound that continues to fill the air.

57
00:03:37,348 --> 00:03:40,420
Lucien looks up again. In the distance, a small passenger plane makes a sharp turn and plummets, veering at an unusual trajectory. Thick black smoke billows from its right wing.

58
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:43,121
A fighter jet closes in from behind as the passenger plane plunges into the distance, skimming beneath the low-hanging clouds.

59
00:03:43,121 --> 00:03:48,320
In an instant, it merges with the smoke.

60
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:51,156
He watches calmly, then looks down to confirm that his message has been sent successfully before turning to leave.

61
00:03:51,156 --> 00:03:53,046
The dust floats in the wind and settles on his shoulder.

62
00:03:53,046 --> 00:03:56,321
In a world where people depart at any moment, he simply reaches out to brush off the dust before walking away in the direction he came from.

63
00:03:57,570 --> 00:04:01,452
*: 意外 (yìwài) is the keyword of this date. It refers to something unforeseen, whether a surprising event or an unfortunate incident. This word generally means "unexpected" or "accident.

64
00:04:01,452 --> 00:04:04,423
But to keep the repetition intact and considering how, more often than not, it carries a slightly negative connotation of things going wrong, I choose to only use "accident"  to translate the word throughout the whole date.

65
00:04:05,436 --> 00:04:08,576
Plop—

66
00:04:08,576 --> 00:04:11,074
Hearing the abrupt noise, I immediately press myself against the wall, shaking as I tighten my grip on the scalpel in my hand.

67
00:04:11,074 --> 00:04:13,201
In my narrow field of vision, a hunched old woman passes by the intersection.

68
00:04:13,201 --> 00:04:16,374
Her figure is shrouded in gray, and with each unsteady step, a patch of nearly black bloodstain on her back comes into view, sending a violent shudder through me.

69
00:04:16,374 --> 00:04:18,434
I finally realize that I haven’t truly escaped death—

70
00:04:18,434 --> 00:04:20,223
I’ve merely fallen from one desperate situation into another.

71
00:04:20,696 --> 00:04:22,586
Three hours ago.

72
00:04:22,586 --> 00:04:24,747
Co-Pilot: We are currently unable to determine the captain’s physical and mental condition...

73
00:04:24,747 --> 00:04:27,617
Co-Pilot: Amid the chaos, the aircraft veered off its autopilot route and entered the airspace of a conflict zone, where it encountered a warning attack...

74
00:04:27,617 --> 00:04:29,912
Co-Pilot: Although we managed to make an emergency landing, the current situation remains unclear...

75
00:04:29,912 --> 00:04:32,140
Co-Pilot: We will continue to do everything possible to contact the airline and relevant authorities.

76
00:04:32,140 --> 00:04:35,078
In a crude medical shelter, with his right arm wrapped in a rough bandage, the co-pilot speaks heavily.

77
00:04:35,078 --> 00:04:37,610
Several fellow passengers frown, wanting to say something, but in the end, it turns into a few muttered curses.

78
00:04:37,610 --> 00:04:40,277
Faced with the absent-minded captain, he almost single-handedly managed to execute an emergency landing in the woods.

79
00:04:40,277 --> 00:04:42,437
He then proceeded to provide emergency bandages to the more seriously injured passengers in an orderly manner.

80
00:04:42,437 --> 00:04:45,341
With the communication equipment failing, he relies on his memory of the flight path before the crash, leading the group toward a possible inhabited area.

81
00:04:45,341 --> 00:04:48,683
It wasn’t until dark that we finally found a rundown bungalow on the city's outskirts, flying a Red Cross flag, where we fortunately received temporary assistance.

82
00:04:48,683 --> 00:04:50,675
Everything feels like some kind of miracle in the midst of immense misfortune.

83
00:04:50,675 --> 00:04:53,207
Co-Pilot: I suggest we stay here for now. This place is relatively safe and on the other hand...

84
00:04:53,207 --> 00:04:55,199
Co-Pilot: We have several seriously injured passengers who can’t be easily moved.

85
00:04:55,199 --> 00:04:57,562
Passenger: Can’t we ask them to go somewhere with a signal and contact the embassy for us?

86
00:04:57,562 --> 00:05:01,005
As the words are spoken, the rushing wind carries a pungent scent of blood. They speak anxiously in a language we don't understand, pushing a surgical trolley as they rush into the building.

87
00:05:01,005 --> 00:05:03,267
They already have their hands full with the constant influx of injured people.

88
00:05:03,267 --> 00:05:05,124
No one speaks again, and I lower my head as well.

89
00:05:05,124 --> 00:05:06,745
By great fortune, I’ve survived the disaster.

90
00:05:06,745 --> 00:05:09,851
Gratitude and trance consume me at the same time. At this moment, I don’t even know how much time has passed—it feels like time has frozen into a blurry black mass.

91
00:05:09,851 --> 00:05:11,539
Will Lucien know that something has happened to me?

92
00:05:11,539 --> 00:05:14,172
Will my flight make the news as a ghost flight? Will he see the reports saying my fate is unknown?

93
00:05:14,172 --> 00:05:16,906
I bite my lips tightly, trying to force my muddled mind to think, but my eyes slowly grow wet.

94
00:05:16,906 --> 00:05:20,181
I can’t even imagine what Lucien would look like at that moment, but I know very well that staying here is the safest and most responsible choice for both him and me.

95
00:05:20,181 --> 00:05:21,835
...I must survive.

96
00:05:22,950 --> 00:05:27,170
Boom—The distant sound of what seems to be a collapse suddenly pulls me back to reality.

97
00:05:27,170 --> 00:05:29,499
We’ve underestimated the level of chaos here; accidents can happen at any moment.

98
00:05:29,499 --> 00:05:31,930
The conflict has reached the camp, and in the urgent evacuation, there’s only a loud noise left in the world.

99
00:05:31,930 --> 00:05:34,901
When I come to my senses, I find myself alone, with nothing but a rust-covered scalpel that I don’t even remember holding.

100
00:05:34,901 --> 00:05:37,466
The streets are even more desolate after dark, and I force myself to stay alert almost instinctively.

101
00:05:37,466 --> 00:05:39,391
What should I do? How can I survive?

102
00:05:39,391 --> 00:05:41,045
Only deathly silence answers me.

103
00:05:41,045 --> 00:05:43,476
I clench my hand repeatedly, trying to force myself to stop trembling, but it’s no use.

104
00:05:43,476 --> 00:05:45,805
Suddenly, a click sounds from behind me, and a cold sweat instantly soaks my skin.

105
00:05:45,805 --> 00:05:47,898
Someone has appeared behind me, stepping on shards of glass.

106
00:05:47,898 --> 00:05:51,139
I tremble so much that I can barely breathe, forcing myself to silently hide the scalpel in my sleeve. Turning around, I raise both hands to show that I mean no harm.

107
00:05:51,139 --> 00:05:53,941
What comes into view is a pair of black leather shoes covered in ashes, yet there’s not a single crease or scuff on them.

108
00:05:53,941 --> 00:05:56,473
They are not combat boots, nor do they bear any traces of blood, which makes me breathe a sudden and grateful sigh of relief.

109
00:05:56,473 --> 00:05:59,613
Perhaps someone from the medical team has found me. With that thought in mind, I lift my head, only to find myself staring into a pair of familiar eyes.

110
00:05:59,613 --> 00:06:02,652
Those dark, indifferent eyes seem to contract intensely the moment they see me.

111
00:06:02,652 --> 00:06:06,129
The world suddenly loses all sound, and on the eerily empty street, Lucien stands across from me.

112
00:06:06,129 --> 00:06:07,277
MC: ….

113
00:06:07,277 --> 00:06:09,201
I don’t dare to move, not even to blink.

114
00:06:09,201 --> 00:06:11,767
It feels like a grand hallucination on the verge of collapse, one that’s ready to burst like a bubble the moment I move.

115
00:06:11,767 --> 00:06:14,299
My blurred vision makes his face even more indistinct, and that figure also seems to walk toward me in a daze.

116
00:06:14,299 --> 00:06:17,371
He, too, seems to hold his breath. His steps gradually quicken, stirring the hem of his coat and the dust in the air until he stops right in front of me.

117
00:06:17,371 --> 00:06:20,511
His chest seems to tremble uncontrollably, and his slightly shaking fingertips fall upon my face. Cold. Undeniably real.

118
00:06:20,511 --> 00:06:22,266
Lucien: …MC?

119
00:06:22,266 --> 00:06:25,372
His low, hoarse voice feels both near and distant, leaving me dazed as I gaze at him, feeling his uneasy yet fearful touch brush against my cheek.

120
00:06:25,372 --> 00:06:27,195
MC: …Lucien, is it really… you?

121
00:06:27,195 --> 00:06:28,917
MC: Am I… going insane?

122
00:06:28,917 --> 00:06:36,513
Lucien: …Fool, how could I… be just your hallucination?

123
00:06:36,513 --> 00:06:38,707
He lifts my hand and brushes it against his cheek as if confirming*.

124
00:06:38,707 --> 00:06:41,543
The cold, dry sensation spreads through my fingertips, and just like that, the tension that had been stretched to its limit finally snaps.

125
00:06:41,543 --> 00:06:42,860
MC: Lucien…..

126
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:44,615
MC: Lucien… I’m… so scared…

127
00:06:44,615 --> 00:06:47,283
I don’t know how I appear in his eyes at this moment. All I want is to hold him tightly. To be held tightly by him.

128
00:06:47,283 --> 00:06:49,815
His unbearably tight embrace brings pain, but it’s the reality I desperately need right now.

129
00:06:49,815 --> 00:06:52,043
This man who has always been effortlessly composed now seems to have lost all sense of restraint.

130
00:06:52,043 --> 00:06:54,811
Lucien: …It’s okay.

131
00:06:54,811 --> 00:06:59,571
Lucien: It’s okay now… MC.

132
00:06:59,571 --> 00:07:01,867
He murmurs the words over and over, I don’t even know if he’s saying them for me or for himself.

133
00:07:01,867 --> 00:07:05,581
Lucien: I’m here…

134
00:07:05,581 --> 00:07:12,164
Lucien: I'm right here by your side... Don't be afraid...

135
00:07:12,164 --> 00:07:15,202
The head resting against my shoulder feels so, so heavy as if something even weightier has sunk into the depth of our souls along with it.

136
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:18,004
I don’t know how long I’ve been crying.

137
00:07:18,004 --> 00:07:21,077
Only when I have finally let out all my emotions and lean into his embrace do I realize that I’ve arrived in a warm place—

138
00:07:21,077 --> 00:07:23,406
Surrounded by irregular rock walls, the air is filled with a damp, mineral scent.

139
00:07:23,406 --> 00:07:25,870
The rising steam soothes my nerves, and I tug at his collar with more ease.

140
00:07:25,870 --> 00:07:27,356
MC: It's okay now, Lucien...

141
00:07:27,356 --> 00:07:28,943
MC: I'm not afraid anymore...

142
00:07:28,943 --> 00:07:31,373
Lucien: I’m afraid.

143
00:07:31,373 --> 00:07:34,344
His voice is so faint it feels like a figment of my imagination. I want to turn my head to look at him but find myself gently and firmly held in his embrace.

144
00:07:34,344 --> 00:07:43,628
Lucien: It’s safe here. I’m staying here for now.

145
00:07:43,628 --> 00:07:46,565
Peering over his shoulder, I see an open door leading to a clean bed, a few sofas, and a table.

146
00:07:46,565 --> 00:07:49,300
In the corner of my vision, a gray toothbrush rests inside a glass cup, and the razor I gave him is neatly placed.

147
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:51,089
I freeze for a moment, feeling like something is off.

148
00:07:51,089 --> 00:07:52,676
MC: Didn’t you say you were on a business trip…?

149
00:07:52,676 --> 00:07:59,023
Lucien: I am, and I’ve indeed been staying here for a few days.

150
00:07:59,023 --> 00:08:05,741
Lucien: I know you must have a lot of questions. To be honest, so do I.

151
00:08:05,741 --> 00:08:12,122
Lucien: But right now… there’s something even more important to me.

152
00:08:12,122 --> 00:08:14,958
Following his lowered gaze, I see the dirt covering me and my tattered clothes, torn in places I don’t know.

153
00:08:14,958 --> 00:08:17,287
My drooping strands of hair are covered in dust, resting against Lucien’s clean shirt.

154
00:08:17,287 --> 00:08:19,009
MC: I got your shirt dirty.

155
00:08:19,009 --> 00:08:22,014
Lucien: ...Stop saying such silly things.

156
00:08:22,014 --> 00:08:24,444
He gently pecks the space between my brows, his fingertips naturally undoing the loosened buttons on my clothes.

157
00:08:24,444 --> 00:08:25,829
MC: Lu—!

158
00:08:25,829 --> 00:08:28,327
Lucien: Shh….

159
00:08:28,327 --> 00:08:30,386
His lips move downward, pressing insistently against the corner of mine.

160
00:08:30,386 --> 00:08:32,243
Though very light, it is filled with an undeniable firmness.

161
00:08:32,243 --> 00:08:37,476
Lucien: Don’t push me away.

162
00:08:37,476 --> 00:08:43,215
Lucien: I also need to confirm that you're really here with me.

163
00:08:43,215 --> 00:08:48,853
Lucien: Let me help you… okay?

164
00:08:48,853 --> 00:08:52,162
It isn’t really a question. His voice lingers at the edge of my lips, flowing with his breath, making my head feel light and dazed. Instinctively, I nod at him.

165
00:08:52,162 --> 00:08:54,862
His fingers move slowly yet deftly. Bit by bit, patches of deep bruises become more visible.

166
00:08:54,862 --> 00:08:56,787
His warmth spreads through me faster than the cold.

167
00:08:56,787 --> 00:09:00,365
I’m too embarrassed to look at him, so I bury my face deep into his chest instead. I feel him scoop me up in his arms and carefully lower me into the bathtub’s warm water.

168
00:09:00,365 --> 00:09:02,661
The sudden heat stings me, jolting me awake as I grab Lucien’s wrist.

169
00:09:02,661 --> 00:09:05,125
MC: Wait, the other passengers I was with, because of the conflict, they’re now…

170
00:09:05,125 --> 00:09:09,784
Lucien: Don’t worry, someone will take care of it.

171
00:09:09,784 --> 00:09:15,389
Lucien: Right now, only you matter the most to me.

172
00:09:15,389 --> 00:09:18,596
There seems to be something growing wildly beneath his calm gaze. He subtly and seamlessly intertwines his fingers with mine, gently submerging my body into the water.

173
00:09:18,596 --> 00:09:22,309
The deep and shallow bruises appear even more striking in the clear water. A dull ache seeps into the water, causing a small, instinctive sigh to spill from my lips.

174
00:09:22,309 --> 00:09:25,111
Lucien: Relax.

175
00:09:25,111 --> 00:09:27,947
He applies slight pressure, gently prying apart my fingers that are curled around my knees. Carefully avoiding the bruises on my thighs, his hand presses downward.

176
00:09:27,947 --> 00:09:29,399
MC: [moans] L-lucien…

177
00:09:29,399 --> 00:09:34,497
Lucien: I just want to help you relax a little more.

178
00:09:34,497 --> 00:09:42,566
Lucien: At least for this moment, be a good girl... okay?

179
00:09:42,566 --> 00:09:44,287
Another question that isn’t really a question.

180
00:09:44,287 --> 00:09:47,697
I can’t get a single word out**, so I can only bite my lower lip, watching as he kneels by the bathtub, a soft towel in his hand, lightly stroking over my arm.

181
00:09:47,697 --> 00:09:50,027
Lucien: Does it hurt?

182
00:09:50,027 --> 00:09:52,592
His low, hoarse voice is caught in his throat as if suppressing something before finally smoothing into a calm steadiness.

183
00:09:52,592 --> 00:09:53,976
MC: …A little.

184
00:09:53,976 --> 00:10:02,788
Lucien: Then I’ll be gentler.

185
00:10:02,788 --> 00:10:05,725
His gentle, unhurried touch warms one arm before moving to the other. Then, it follows the top of my foot, slowly moving upward.

186
00:10:05,725 --> 00:10:08,763
As he leans down, his large shadow envelops my whole body, and I instinctively tremble with each faint mark he leaves behind.

187
00:10:08,763 --> 00:10:11,836
Something seems to be stirring madly in his calm gaze, suppressed within his silence, driving him to confirm me even more deeply and intimately.

188
00:10:11,836 --> 00:10:14,840
I feel as if I’m sinking into the warm water, yet also weightlessly floating with it, my hands instinctively clutching the fabric at his chest tightly.

189
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:20,276
Lucien: …bear with it a little longer… wait for me...

190
00:10:20,276 --> 00:10:23,044
As if to soothe, his even more scorching lips descend, teasingly hooking and coaxing my lips and tongue, relentlessly drawing me in.

191
00:10:23,044 --> 00:10:25,981
At some point, his entire body has also become drenched, his drooping bangs soaked with water, revealing those unfathomably profound eyes.

192
00:10:25,981 --> 00:10:32,159
Lucien: I'll help you get rid of all the pain.

193
00:10:32,801 --> 00:10:35,805
*: the wording in Chinese is ambiguous; it could mean either that he is making sure she’s not his hallucination or that he’s reassuring her that he’s real :") and this ambiguousness HURTS because-

194
00:10:35,805 --> 00:10:39,654
you know that he also has the same fear as her (this will be expanded more later on memory silhouette). This guy really said, "…Fool, how could I… be just your hallucination?" yet he’s in disbelief himself that she’s real and I’m just SOB-

195
00:10:39,654 --> 00:10:42,591
**: 说不出任何话 literally means "can't say any words at all." However, the nuance is deeper than just the inability to speak. It can imply being so overwhelmed by emotions (orcoughpleasurecough) that speaking becomes impossible.

196
00:10:42,591 --> 00:10:44,009
Besides being overwhelmed, it’s also often used when somebody wants to say something but physically/emotionally just cannot.

197
00:10:44,617 --> 00:10:48,398
Even when carried to the bed, my whole body still feels light and weightless.

198
00:10:48,398 --> 00:10:51,470
An oversized shirt is put over me, its scent different from the dense smell of gunpowder as it carries the light freshness of grass that I’m familiar with.

199
00:10:51,470 --> 00:10:54,812
Lucien casually changes into fresh clothes, grabs a few towels, then pulls me into his arms and smooths back my damp hair.

200
00:10:54,812 --> 00:10:56,399
MC: …How about I do it myself?

201
00:10:56,399 --> 00:10:58,830
MC: It’s inconvenient for you like this, and it’ll just get your clothes wet again.

202
00:10:58,830 --> 00:11:08,080
Lucien: But it seems my hands can’t let go of you… they need your warmth even more.

203
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:11,591
His gentle yet firm fingertips stroke the back of my neck, resting the side of my forehead against his shoulder. His legs settle on either side of me, enclosing me within his territory.

204
00:11:11,591 --> 00:11:14,022
The world is enveloped in tranquility, with only the rustling sound of a towel rubbing against damp hair remaining.

205
00:11:14,022 --> 00:11:16,318
MC: It must be pretty inconvenient for you here too, there’s not even a hairdryer.

206
00:11:16,318 --> 00:11:22,563
Lucien: Don’t worry, the equipment here is a bit more complete than you think.

207
00:11:22,563 --> 00:11:24,758
His low voice brushes past my ear, making me look up in confusion.

208
00:11:24,758 --> 00:11:26,243
MC: Then why do you…

209
00:11:26,243 --> 00:11:32,421
Lucien: Sound of the hairdryer would make you uncomfortable, so this will do.

210
00:11:32,421 --> 00:11:35,831
I freeze for a moment. That trace of distant rumble and roar still seems to be howling, yet at this moment, they appear to settle into a quiet stillness within his deep eyes.

211
00:11:35,831 --> 00:11:38,633
Only now do I notice more clearly that he seems to be slowing down his breathing as if he's cradling something fragile.

212
00:11:38,633 --> 00:11:40,490
MC: …Do I look like a total mess?

213
00:11:40,490 --> 00:11:50,348
Lucien: How could that be? To me, I never would have imagined that in a place as desolate and ruined as this…

214
00:11:50,348 --> 00:11:54,332
Lucien: I could still be lucky enough to encounter such a beautiful and resilient color.

215
00:11:54,332 --> 00:12:00,678
Lucien: Even though I never wanted you to be here.

216
00:12:00,678 --> 00:12:10,570
Lucien: I can’t help but wonder… if I hadn’t stepped out the door today if I hadn’t turned left...

217
00:12:10,570 --> 00:12:12,832
His words come to an abrupt halt, followed quickly by a faint chuckle that carries a touch of self-mockery.

218
00:12:12,832 --> 00:12:15,128
Like a staunch materialist*, yet hesitating over irrational ‘what ifs’.

219
00:12:15,128 --> 00:12:17,930
The rhythmic beating of his heart echoes in my ears, but that subtle, unintentional quickening of its pace seems to take on another name—

220
00:12:17,930 --> 00:12:19,382
It’s called ‘lingering fear’**.

221
00:12:19,382 --> 00:12:22,555
The arm holding me seems to tighten in the next moment, and I can’t help but clutch the front of his shirt, burrowing myself even deeper into his embrace.

222
00:12:22,555 --> 00:12:27,754
Lucien: Right now, I’m already by your side.

223
00:12:27,754 --> 00:12:33,932
Lucien: I’ll take responsibility for driving away all those unpleasant things lingering in your brain.

224
00:12:33,932 --> 00:12:35,316
MC: Really?

225
00:12:35,316 --> 00:12:37,646
Lucien smiles lightly, and the tension in his brows and eyes finally eases slightly.

226
00:12:37,646 --> 00:12:46,592
Lucien: As a brain scientist, it would be difficult for me to lie to you about this.

227
00:12:46,592 --> 00:12:49,023
Seeing him feign seriousness while explaining, I can’t hide my laughter at his dry joke.

228
00:12:49,023 --> 00:12:51,082
MC: Lucien, let me tell you about my brush with death.

229
00:12:51,082 --> 00:12:53,176
MC: Maybe facing it head-on will make it less frightening.

230
00:12:53,176 --> 00:12:55,066
Lucien doesn’t speak for a moment, only silently changing to a new towel.

231
00:12:55,066 --> 00:12:57,801
I rarely see him like this, so I can’t resist reaching out and gently smooth the furrow between his brows.

232
00:12:57,801 --> 00:12:59,556
MC: Do you want to hear it?

233
00:12:59,556 --> 00:13:04,654
Lucien: …Perhaps, the one who is more afraid is me.

234
00:13:04,654 --> 00:13:07,119
He closes his eyes, presses a light kiss to my fingertips, and finally looks at me with an even deeper calm.

235
00:13:07,119 --> 00:13:11,642
Lucien: I’ll do my best to hold back the ache in my heart and listen carefully.

236
00:13:11,642 --> 00:13:13,668
MC: Lucien, you’re just as much a fool as I am.

237
00:13:13,668 --> 00:13:20,690
Lucien: You're probably the only person in the world who would praise me like that.

238
00:13:20,690 --> 00:13:22,716
In his tender, lingering kisses, I finally steady my mind.

239
00:13:22,716 --> 00:13:25,248
MC: Actually, I still don’t have a clear understanding of what exactly happened during that time.

240
00:13:25,248 --> 00:13:27,442
MC: I only heard the co-pilot say that the captain suddenly had some kind of mental issue…?

241
00:13:27,442 --> 00:13:29,907
MC: Later, our plane accidentally entered a no-fly zone, was threatened, and ultimately had to make an emergency landing.

242
00:13:29,907 --> 00:13:32,101
Lucien's breathing seems to have stagnated for a moment, and his eyes droop slightly.

243
00:13:32,101 --> 00:13:37,672
Lucien: Your plane… Did the right wing get hit?

244
00:13:37,672 --> 00:13:39,225
MC: Hmm? It seems... to be true?

245
00:13:39,225 --> 00:13:42,060
MC: I was sitting on the plane's right side at the time, and all I could see was black smoke. But I was so scared then that I couldn't really tell...

246
00:13:42,060 --> 00:13:44,862
Recalling that scene, I still instinctively curl up in lingering fear, not noticing the way his eyes suddenly contract sharply.

247
00:13:44,862 --> 00:13:47,597
MC: But luckily, everyone was safe. We just kept walking and were rescued by a local civilian medical organization.

248
00:13:47,597 --> 00:13:50,332
MC: But the scene was too chaotic. Later, the gathering site was also affected, and I got separated from the main group during the evacuation.

249
00:13:50,332 --> 00:13:52,290
I pause, looking into his eyes with mixed emotions.

250
00:13:52,290 --> 00:13:53,978
MC: And then I met you.

251
00:13:53,978 --> 00:13:55,632
MC: …All of this is just too unbelievable.

252
00:13:55,632 --> 00:13:58,502
MC: The accidents in this world really catch people completely off guard. I feel like I’ve had the worst luck… but at the same time, I also seem exceptionally fortunate.

253
00:13:58,502 --> 00:14:00,764
Lucien: ….

254
00:14:00,764 --> 00:14:02,722
He falls silent again, it's unclear what he is thinking.

255
00:14:02,722 --> 00:14:05,591
I don’t know how much time has passed. After ensuring my hair has been completely dried, he casually throws the damp towels aside.

256
00:14:05,591 --> 00:14:08,191
The world suddenly quiets down, and Lucien wordlessly raises his hand, his fingertips gently brushing over the bruises on my body.

257
00:14:08,191 --> 00:14:10,284
As our skin touches, a slight itch ripples through my skin, accompanied by an extremely faint pain sensation.

258
00:14:10,284 --> 00:14:12,715
Thinking of his ‘confirmation’ in the bathtub not long ago, I can’t help but feel my face grow slightly warm again.

259
00:14:12,715 --> 00:14:15,247
I lift my head and kiss the corner of his lips, lingering until our breaths intertwine, then smile and wink at him.

260
00:14:15,247 --> 00:14:17,070
MC: Don’t worry. With you here, I already feel much better.

261
00:14:17,070 --> 00:14:19,433
MC: When I get up tomorrow, I’ll definitely return to full strength. Then, we can…

262
00:14:19,433 --> 00:14:21,459
As I speak, I suddenly stop, realizing something.

263
00:14:21,459 --> 00:14:23,417
MC: Are we... still near this area?

264
00:14:23,417 --> 00:14:25,240
Seeing him respond softly, my heart tightens.

265
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:28,109
MC: You said you’ve been here for a few days, so that closed-off lab you mentioned... is it here?

266
00:14:28,109 --> 00:14:30,371
Lucien: Yes.

267
00:14:30,371 --> 00:14:36,414
Lucien: Even though this place is far from tranquil, I have a reason that makes it necessary for me to be here.

268
00:14:36,414 --> 00:14:39,014
His voice possesses a certain indifference and resolve. I gaze at him for a moment before slowly speaking.

269
00:14:39,014 --> 00:14:40,736
MC: Are you doing something dangerous?

270
00:14:40,736 --> 00:14:41,951
Lucien: ….

271
00:14:41,951 --> 00:14:45,428
Under my gaze, Lucien remains silent for a long time, long enough that I almost think he will find some way to sidestep the topic until his low voice finally breaks the silence.

272
00:14:45,428 --> 00:14:51,539
Lucien: The research institution I’m working with now is one I had contact with years ago when I first joined BS.

273
00:14:51,539 --> 00:15:00,688
Lucien: They have a considerable amount of multinational projects, as well as some that can hardly be called ethical or compliant. In one way or another, some covert dealings are involved.

274
00:15:00,688 --> 00:15:07,035
Lucien: All I can say is, yes. The things I’m doing are not safe.

275
00:15:07,035 --> 00:15:13,821
Lucien: So I hope you don’t go anywhere and just stay by my side.

276
00:15:13,821 --> 00:15:15,981
Seeing him be especially frank about his thoughts, I can’t hold back my smile.

277
00:15:15,981 --> 00:15:18,344
MC: Lucien, I'm not asking about myself, I'm asking if you will be in danger.

278
00:15:18,344 --> 00:15:20,708
He freezes for a moment, then smiles without the slightest hesitation.

279
00:15:20,708 --> 00:15:23,408
Lucien: No, I won’t.

280
00:15:23,408 --> 00:15:28,304
Lucien: I should be able to get what I want soon, so don’t worry.

281
00:15:28,304 --> 00:15:30,667
He presses a light kiss to my forehead, pulls back the blanket, and wraps me in its softness.

282
00:15:30,667 --> 00:15:38,466
Lucien: But… I think that’s enough of a bedtime story for now.

283
00:15:38,466 --> 00:15:48,526
Lucien: Just like you said, I want to see you full of energy as soon as possible, smiling without any worries or strain.

284
00:15:48,526 --> 00:15:51,024
Looking at his incredibly close face, I smile and lean in closer to his scent.

285
00:15:51,024 --> 00:15:52,847
MC: What should I do? I’m still a little reluctant to sleep.

286
00:15:52,847 --> 00:15:55,312
MC: It might be a bit late to say this now, but after so many days apart, I’ve really missed you all along.

287
00:15:55,312 --> 00:15:57,641
Lucien: Me too.

288
00:15:57,641 --> 00:16:09,154
Lucien: So all you need to do is close your eyes, I will always let you feel my presence and longing.

289
00:16:10,268 --> 00:16:12,327
Like finally returning to the most secure and reassuring home***, I relax and close my eyes.

290
00:16:12,327 --> 00:16:15,230
One after another, incomparably intimate and affectionate kisses fall upon my face and between my lips, as if scattering in tiny, delicate fragments that sink into the depths of my heart—

291
00:16:15,230 --> 00:16:16,918
—until I fall into an exceedingly gentle dream.

292
00:16:18,134 --> 00:16:19,687
When I open my eyes again, daylight is already shining brightly.

293
00:16:19,687 --> 00:16:22,489
Lucien isn’t by the bed. As I get up and step out of bed, I notice that my wounds seem to have been tended once more.

294
00:16:22,489 --> 00:16:23,772
MC: Lucien…?

295
00:16:23,772 --> 00:16:26,675
The room is quiet. Breakfast is laid out on the table, along with a laptop and a slightly old-fashioned phone.

296
00:16:26,675 --> 00:16:29,005
He hasn’t left a note, but I still smile with an unspoken understanding.

297
00:16:29,005 --> 00:16:33,056
I’m just about to wash up when the phone screen suddenly lights up. A message pops up, showing Lucien’s number.

298
00:16:33,056 --> 00:16:35,250
Lucien's message: Good morning MC. I’m already at the lab.

299
00:16:35,250 --> 00:16:37,850
Lucien's message: I’ve arranged for someone to contact and assist the passengers who were with you, so there’s no need to worry.

300
00:16:37,850 --> 00:16:40,618
Lucien's message: I’ve also informed your company that you’re safe. Work matters can be left to them for now.

301
00:16:40,618 --> 00:16:43,285
Lucien's message: Get some rest, I’ll return as soon as I can.

302
00:16:43,285 --> 00:16:45,615
Sunlight spills in from the balcony, and a gentle breeze brushes against my face, carrying a touch of winter’s coldness.

303
00:16:45,615 --> 00:16:48,012
Yet, I don’t feel the biting cold. Instead, there’s a sense of warmth and security.

304
00:16:48,012 --> 00:16:50,746
Though the scene before me remains desolate and ruined, the world feels tranquil right now, free of the terrifying tumultuous noise.

305
00:16:50,746 --> 00:16:53,852
I step onto the balcony and see golden light magnanimously illuminating the earth. A small bird perches under the eaves, occasionally lowering its head to preen its feathers.

306
00:16:53,852 --> 00:16:56,519
A faint wave of emotion wells up in my heart. Perhaps this place would have been entirely different if not for all the turmoil.

307
00:16:56,519 --> 00:16:58,275
But what I’ve never noticed is—

308
00:16:58,275 --> 00:17:00,131
—the little bird on the eaves has only one wing.

309
00:17:00,604 --> 00:17:02,596
*: In this date, it’s Materialism in philosophical context rather than everyday use.  Materialism is a philosophical belief that only physical matter exists and that everything can be explained through the physical world and natural laws.

310
00:17:02,596 --> 00:17:04,655
Lucien mocks himself for speculating about "what ifs", because it involves considering possibilities that may have no empirical grounding, which contradicts materialist core belief that only the physical matters.

311
00:17:04,655 --> 00:17:07,457
**: “后怕" refers to lingering/delayed fear, realizing the terror of something only after it has passed. He has just come to the realization of how close he was to losing her forever, and it filled him with 后怕. In some contexts, it can even be directly translated into PTSD.

312
00:17:07,457 --> 00:17:09,719
***: "归处" (guīchù) means both "home" and "place of belonging." So for MC, Lucien is not just a home to return to but a refuge where her heart finds peace, like a final destination of solace and stability.

313
00:17:10,158 --> 00:17:13,669
As expected, everything has been thoroughly taken care of by Lucien.

314
00:17:13,669 --> 00:17:16,843
Upon seeing on the laptop that the embassy had already contacted the local government to carry out the rescue operation, the last bit of unease in my heart vanished into thin air.

315
00:17:16,843 --> 00:17:19,814
Thinking of how Lucien told me not to wander around, I simply grab one of his books to read and wait for him in the room.

316
00:17:19,814 --> 00:17:23,662
Before I realize it, the light of setting sun slants, casting its glow onto the coffee table. Amid my drowsiness, my phone suddenly rings.

317
00:17:23,662 --> 00:17:26,093
MC: Are you done with work?

318
00:17:26,093 --> 00:17:30,313
Lucien: Mm. Are you doing okay?

319
00:17:30,313 --> 00:17:33,892
MC: I’m fine. I was just reading the book you left on the sofa, but it’s so abstruse I almost fell asleep.

320
00:17:33,892 --> 00:17:39,968
Lucien: To be honest, I’ve dozed off on that book more than a few times myself too.

321
00:17:39,968 --> 00:17:43,209
As we chat and laugh, I stroll to the balcony under the slowly fading glow of the sunset.

322
00:17:43,209 --> 00:17:46,856
Lucien: I should be back very soon.

323
00:17:46,856 --> 00:17:51,920
MC: Then I’ll check what’s left in the fridge and see what I can cook. Maybe I can cook a big hodgepodge~

324
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:55,498
I smile as I hang up the phone and look up, only to see the same little bird from this morning still perched on the eaves.

325
00:17:55,498 --> 00:17:59,921
—No different from the scene I saw before.

326
00:17:59,921 --> 00:18:05,390
It still preening its feathers, never stopping for even a second, nor ever lifting its head.

327
00:18:05,390 --> 00:18:09,374
It's as if it were a lifeless shadow, mechanically repeating the same motions repeatedly.

328
00:18:09,374 --> 00:18:13,898
A chill spreads through my heart, and I unconsciously feel a bit of panic. Suddenly, I notice that the scene before me carries an absurd sense of repetition—

329
00:18:13,898 --> 00:18:17,915
At times, a passerby would cross to the end of the street only to abruptly reappear on the other side.

330
00:18:17,915 --> 00:18:23,249
The distant edges of the city also seem indescribably blurred, as if detached from reality, carved apart by dividing borders.

331
00:18:24,498 --> 00:18:28,752
I try to calm down and cautiously push open the door.

332
00:18:28,752 --> 00:18:33,040
The dark-colored walls on either side are clean yet monotonous, showing no signs of anything unusual.

333
00:18:33,040 --> 00:18:35,740
After thinking about it, I step through the doorway. But the farther I walk, the more cold sweat seeps down my back.

334
00:18:35,740 --> 00:18:38,475
There is no elevator here nor any emergency exit.

335
00:18:38,475 --> 00:18:41,007
The dim corridor seems endless, with the same unchanging scenery stretching ahead and behind.

336
00:18:41,007 --> 00:18:43,573
As my nerves gradually tighten, I suddenly catch sight of a warm yellow light at the end of the corridor.

337
00:18:43,573 --> 00:18:45,936
I immediately run toward it—

338
00:18:47,016 --> 00:18:50,325
Until that glow envelops me, and I freeze in place.

339
00:18:50,325 --> 00:18:56,840
I find myself back in the room again.

340
00:18:56,840 --> 00:19:02,613
The space that once felt reassuring now makes me feel like I can’t breathe.

341
00:19:02,613 --> 00:19:07,779
Even though I’ve experienced similar situations before, I still can’t help but wonder… could all of this be nothing more than a fleeting hallucination* inside my mind?

342
00:19:07,779 --> 00:19:12,843
But the voice I just heard was gentle and real, and the spot where he lay still retains a faint warmth.

343
00:19:12,843 --> 00:19:15,847
??(Lucien): …MC…

344
00:19:15,847 --> 00:19:20,405
I keep comforting myself not to fall into post-traumatic stress. Lucien said he is here conducting research, maybe this strange phenomenon is also related to his work.

345
00:19:20,405 --> 00:19:23,950
?? (Lucien): MC, are you okay?

346
00:19:23,950 --> 00:19:28,305
In a daze, a warm palm seems to lift me from the depths of the sea, bringing me back to the surface.

347
00:19:29,925 --> 00:19:34,145
I blink and suddenly see Lucien standing before me, his face filled with worry as he cups my cheeks. I have no idea when he got there.

348
00:19:34,145 --> 00:19:36,171
MC: Lucien…

349
00:19:36,171 --> 00:19:40,830
Lucien: Are you feeling unwell anywhere?

350
00:19:40,830 --> 00:19:44,679
I open my mouth, momentarily at a loss. Lucien immediately pulls me into a tighter embrace.

351
00:19:44,679 --> 00:19:49,675
Lucien: It's my fault.

352
00:19:49,675 --> 00:19:57,373
Lucien: You're not in a good state right now. I should have spent more time with you.

353
00:19:57,373 --> 00:20:10,370
Lucien: It’ll be over soon, just hold on a little longer. Soon… we’ll be able to go home together.

354
00:20:10,370 --> 00:20:13,679
His warmth presses against me, enveloping my whole body. I take a deep breath and gently pat him.

355
00:20:13,679 --> 00:20:16,413
MC: Don’t worry, Lucien. I’m fine.

356
00:20:16,413 --> 00:20:19,182
Looking at his raised face, I feel a pang of heartache as I brush over his slightly bloodshot eyes. Tentatively, I ask him.

357
00:20:19,182 --> 00:20:22,895
MC: Are you working on some kind of Evol-related research?

358
00:20:22,895 --> 00:20:27,149
Lucien: Why do you ask?

359
00:20:27,149 --> 00:20:31,302
MC: Maybe I'm overthinking it… but I can't shake the feeling that everything outside this room seems unreal.

360
00:20:31,302 --> 00:20:35,690
He seems startled for a moment, his entire figure hidden in the shadows.

361
00:20:35,690 --> 00:20:41,463
Heavy emotions surge within his dark eyes as he presses his forehead to mine, swallowing my whole reflection into them.

362
00:20:41,463 --> 00:20:46,021
Lucien: Then do you think I’m unreal?

363
00:20:46,021 --> 00:20:50,140
MC: Of course not!

364
00:20:50,140 --> 00:20:55,001
MC: I just... suddenly discover that the corridor outside the door seems endless, so...

365
00:20:55,001 --> 00:20:59,019
Lucien: I see.

366
00:21:00,234 --> 00:21:07,695
He gently takes my hand and leads me outside. We move smoothly through the corridor, take the elevator, and leave the apartment without any trouble.

367
00:21:07,695 --> 00:21:12,928
The night is quiet, and there are hardly any people along the way.

368
00:21:12,928 --> 00:21:17,249
Seeing my stunned expression, Lucien smiles and tightens his hold on my hand.

369
00:21:17,249 --> 00:21:25,115
Lucien: I think the best way to comfort you right now is to take a walk, just like we always do.

370
00:21:25,115 --> 00:21:32,441
Lucien: Although this place isn’t exactly peaceful, at least this neighborhood is not dangerous.

371
00:21:32,441 --> 00:21:37,033
He pauses for a moment, then continues explaining in a gentle voice.

372
00:21:37,033 --> 00:21:45,203
Lucien: The result I await has nothing to do with Evol. It is an experiment in the field of neuroscience.

373
00:21:45,203 --> 00:21:52,967
Lucien: However, the test samples are extremely fragile and require strict control over variables such as temperature and humidity.

374
00:21:52,967 --> 00:22:06,168
Lucien: Therefore, special devices have been installed near the laboratory to restrict Evol, eliminating interference factors and preserving the samples’ activity.

375
00:22:06,168 --> 00:22:11,097
I listen thoughtfully, unable to resist asking another question.

376
00:22:11,097 --> 00:22:14,979
MC: ...So what I saw was really an effect of the experiment?

377
00:22:14,979 --> 00:22:19,064
Lucien gives a noncommittal smile, adjusting my scarf snugly before we continue walking through the quiet neighborhood.

378
00:22:20,246 --> 00:22:25,546
In the following days, Lucien maintains a highly regular work schedule and calls me every now and then.

379
00:22:25,546 --> 00:22:29,699
I have a vague feeling that my accident, combined with my previous state, may have truly frightened him badly. He seems even more attentive to me than before.

380
00:22:29,699 --> 00:22:33,682
I put down the book in my hands and look toward the door again.

381
00:22:33,682 --> 00:22:37,801
Actually, I’ve tried going out on my own since then, but for some reason, whenever I’m alone, I end up circling back to where I started—

382
00:22:37,801 --> 00:22:41,380
As if I’m trapped inside the room.

383
00:22:41,380 --> 00:22:45,093
The vague sense of confinement only makes me even more curious about what Lucien is really doing, so I start searching around.

384
00:22:45,093 --> 00:22:49,381
Before long, I found a report on the Holden Research Institute, which seems to contain a list of personnel and medication records.

385
00:22:49,381 --> 00:22:53,229
As my eyes scan the unfamiliar faces, they all appear ordinary and unremarkable.

386
00:22:53,229 --> 00:22:57,922
Until a familiar face enters my sight, making my eyes widen in shock—

387
00:22:57,922 --> 00:23:02,176
The captain of my flight is among them!

388
00:23:02,176 --> 00:23:06,160
Reading through the information, I find that the captain turns out to be a retired soldier. He has been taking this medication long-term to treat post-war trauma.

389
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:11,224
The records also show that the drug has a small probability of causing neurasthenia, emotional intensification, and even brief episodes of shock…

390
00:23:11,224 --> 00:23:15,916
I involuntarily break out in a cold sweat as I see these people’s data being continuously recorded and updated, even as recently as two weeks ago.

391
00:23:17,537 --> 00:23:27,226
Lucien: Are you saying that the pilot responsible for the accident is on this medication record list?

392
00:23:27,226 --> 00:23:31,750
MC: …Yes.

393
00:23:31,750 --> 00:23:36,037
When Lucien returns that day, I hesitate but eventually tell him about my discovery.

394
00:23:36,037 --> 00:23:40,933
He sits on the sofa, not saying a word for a long time, his entire being sinking into some kind of heavy and terrifying silence.

395
00:23:40,933 --> 00:23:47,415
Lucien: …It seems there really is no need to continue with them.

396
00:23:47,415 --> 00:23:52,715
Lucien: I will put an end to all of this as soon as possible.

397
00:23:52,715 --> 00:23:56,969
He flicks his fingertips, tossing the stack of data reports into the fireplace.

398
00:23:56,969 --> 00:24:01,796
As the flames burn, the charred traces seem to reach all the way into his eyes.

399
00:24:01,796 --> 00:24:07,130
Somehow, I seem to see even darker emotions burning within them, and I can't resist reaching out to stroke his cheek.

400
00:24:07,130 --> 00:24:10,439
MC: Lucien, are you okay?

401
00:24:10,439 --> 00:24:16,009
Lucien: ...MC, are you really here in front of me?

402
00:24:16,009 --> 00:24:19,318
His gaze is deep and distant, yet it firmly holds my gaze in place.

403
00:24:19,318 --> 00:24:25,395
I look at him for a moment, and in that empty gaze, I seem to see a reflection of something similar to myself.

404
00:24:25,395 --> 00:24:29,075
So I move even closer and straddle his lap.

405
00:24:29,075 --> 00:24:35,489
MC: Of course I am. I'm right here with you.

406
00:24:35,489 --> 00:24:39,945
Within his raised gaze, my hand slowly glides toward his sharp jawline.

407
00:24:39,945 --> 00:24:45,212
The artery on the side of his neck subtly swells with each swallow, and with every heartbeat, they pulse steadily yet distinctly beneath my fingertips.

408
00:24:45,212 --> 00:24:50,850
I slightly tilt my face downward, leaning in closer to him. My lips gently graze his, coaxing them to part ever so slightly.

409
00:24:50,850 --> 00:24:56,555
He stares without blinking, watching as in our mingling breaths, my tongue tentatively flicks out to softly lick his upper lip.

410
00:24:56,555 --> 00:25:01,518
It is a test, a touch, and also a reassurance.

411
00:25:01,518 --> 00:25:07,257
I swirl my tongue around his, while Lucien simply follows along, letting himself be led by me.

412
00:25:07,257 --> 00:25:12,727
I can clearly see the corners of his eyes gradually tinged with red, while the pulse at the side of his neck throbs with escalating intensity.

413
00:25:12,727 --> 00:25:16,812
MC: Lucien, tell me, am I in front of you?

414
00:25:16,812 --> 00:25:24,914
Lucien: Yes. You are in front of me.

415
00:25:24,914 --> 00:25:32,713
His voice also seems to catch fire, burning over, searing into his neck as it arches even further, tracing a suggestive arc.

416
00:25:32,713 --> 00:25:40,646
His indulgence unleashes me boundlessly. I can’t help but venture even closer to his breath, brushing past the scorching heat of his chest, trailing all the way downward.

417
00:25:40,646 --> 00:25:45,845
MC: Then... are you in front of me?

418
00:25:45,845 --> 00:25:51,855
Amid the overflowing sultry heat, I can’t stop myself from lifting my body and pushing things further by settling on top of him.

419
00:25:51,855 --> 00:25:57,189
A muffled, unbearable groan slips past his lips. His hand instinctively tightens on my waist, pulling me even closer to him.

420
00:25:57,189 --> 00:26:04,683
Lucien: …Yes… I am in front of you.

421
00:26:04,683 --> 00:26:10,929
His heartbeat seems to throb inside my body, and mine does too.

422
00:26:10,929 --> 00:26:16,094
Countless trembles surge and collide through the bloodstream, even the instinctive sighs spilling from our lips becoming tangled together.

423
00:26:16,094 --> 00:26:22,374
At some point, the fire in the hearth dims, and the dim light of the night blurs into a chaotic and ambiguous interplay of light and shadow.

424
00:26:22,374 --> 00:26:27,978
I can feel his whole body relaxing, and I can’t help but hold him even tighter.

425
00:26:27,978 --> 00:26:32,131
MC: How wonderful, Lucien. You're here by my side.

426
00:26:32,131 --> 00:26:38,275
In the darkness, Lucien stays silent for a moment. Only after what feels like an eternity does his reply drift slowly through the air.

427
00:26:38,275 --> 00:26:45,736
Lucien: Why are you the one offering comfort now... shouldn’t it be me?

428
00:26:45,736 --> 00:26:51,070
MC: Because... even though I’m the one who’s scared, you seem to be afraid of something too.

429
00:26:51,070 --> 00:26:56,573
Lucien: But you should have more important questions to ask me.

430
00:26:56,573 --> 00:27:07,039
Lucien: You should ask me why that drug list is here, or even…

431
00:27:07,039 --> 00:27:13,487
Lucien: Ask whether any of this could possibly be connected to me.

432
00:27:13,487 --> 00:27:17,707
His calm question carries an indescribable scrutiny and simmering anger, leaving me momentarily stunned.

433
00:27:17,707 --> 00:27:23,986
Only now do I belatedly realize the implication of his words. I had almost instinctively not linked Lucien to this matter.

434
00:27:23,986 --> 00:27:28,240
MC: But this drug is essentially used to treat stress-related trauma?

435
00:27:28,240 --> 00:27:32,595
MC: There must be flaws in the screening process that allowed someone taking this medication to become a captain...?

436
00:27:32,595 --> 00:27:36,883
MC: And even if we take a huge step back, if this drug really is connected to you, it’s not like you caused the crash to happen.

437
00:27:36,883 --> 00:27:41,136
MC: As Professor Lucien would usually say, this is just a low-probability event. A mere accident.

438
00:27:41,136 --> 00:27:47,348
Lucien: I don’t like this kind of accident.

439
00:27:47,348 --> 00:27:52,986
He speaks with a stubborn edge, his tone even somewhat stiff and cold.

440
00:27:52,986 --> 00:27:58,860
Like a butterfly with fluttering wings, the massive waves it stirred up should never have crashed upon me.

441
00:27:58,860 --> 00:28:04,431
I only find him endearing and can't resist wanting to peck the corner of his lips.

442
00:28:04,431 --> 00:28:13,918
But in the next second, I’m suddenly picked up. The world spins, and amidst the dizzying whirl, my body is pinned against the sofa in a position difficult to break free from.

443
00:28:13,918 --> 00:28:19,218
My cheek pressed against the cushion, making me unable to see Lucien’s expression at this moment.

444
00:28:19,218 --> 00:28:24,653
With each breath I can sense the fine texture of the fabric, carrying a hint of warmth yet also a subtle, constraining sense of oppression.

445
00:28:24,653 --> 00:28:32,317
Lucien: I don’t like accidents taking you to places I don’t know about.

446
00:28:32,317 --> 00:28:39,677
Lucien: I also don’t like accidents making you go through things I’m unaware of.

447
00:28:39,677 --> 00:28:52,067
Lucien: I dislike it even more when accidents leave bruises that don't belong to me on your body.

448
00:28:52,067 --> 00:28:58,582
As his words trail off, one of his hands seems to trace along my wrist, gliding up my arm to my shoulder, neck, and back.

449
00:28:58,582 --> 00:29:05,368
His burning fingertips travel all the way down my spine, and I can only feel his touch, my body instinctively letting out a trembling shudder.

450
00:29:05,368 --> 00:29:13,369
Lucien: It almost made you disappear.

451
00:29:13,369 --> 00:29:20,796
I feel a firm and increasingly invasive dominant pressure pressing against me from behind, making me bite down my lower lip.

452
00:29:20,796 --> 00:29:26,299
But before I can even utter a word, Lucien overwhelms me almost instantly.

453
00:29:26,299 --> 00:29:30,992
It's as if we're two sheets of dampened paper, growing so wet that we seep into each other.

454
00:29:30,992 --> 00:29:36,698
Without realizing it, we become more and more soaked, until we seem to meld into a single sheet.

455
00:29:36,698 --> 00:29:43,112
I feel as if I've sunk into a deep daze, only aware of him holding me even tighter, pulling me back into his embrace again and again, each time closer than before.

456
00:29:43,112 --> 00:29:48,345
Lucien: MC, you should be angry.

457
00:29:48,345 --> 00:29:53,645
Waves of tingling pleasure continuously spread down my spine, and his voice, filled with frustration, reaches me in a hazy blur.

458
00:29:53,645 --> 00:29:59,925
A dizzy haze endlessly clouds my mind, and I instinctively bite down on a gasp, unable to stop myself from turning my head to look at him.

459
00:29:59,925 --> 00:30:05,124
His face is shrouded in shadows, making his expression even more obscure and harder to discern.

460
00:30:05,124 --> 00:30:09,884
MC: Do you want me to be angry?

461
00:30:09,884 --> 00:30:16,973
Lucien: I don’t know.

462
00:30:16,973 --> 00:30:22,578
He quietly half-kneels there, his voice particularly low and subdued.

463
00:30:22,578 --> 00:30:27,203
MC: Are you trying to punish yourself this way?

464
00:30:27,203 --> 00:30:31,625
MC: You’re angry at yourself, aren’t you?

465
00:30:31,625 --> 00:30:38,006
He still doesn't say anything. He only leans down, pressing his body even deeper into mine. At the same time, his fingers slip between mine, locking our hands together with even more force.

466
00:30:38,006 --> 00:30:42,327
A long time passes before I finally hear his voice from behind me.

467
00:30:42,327 --> 00:30:51,173
Lucien: I almost... lost you again.

468
00:30:51,173 --> 00:30:57,249
The word ‘again’ sinks into my heart, sending a painful ache through me.

469
00:30:57,249 --> 00:31:02,010
MC: Lucien, I want to see you.

470
00:31:02,010 --> 00:31:06,804
MC: Let me see how you are, okay?

471
00:31:06,804 --> 00:31:11,901
Though he doesn’t retreat even half a step, he still yields to my request.

472
00:31:11,901 --> 00:31:18,181
Slowly, he turns me around, finally letting me see his eyes.

473
00:31:18,181 --> 00:31:22,468
Dark. Frenzied. Profoundly raw.***

474
00:31:22,468 --> 00:31:27,836
Too many indescribable emotions surge in those eyes, rising like sky-high waves, sweeping me along with them.

475
00:31:27,836 --> 00:31:32,529
MC: You haven’t lost me, Lucien.

476
00:31:32,529 --> 00:31:41,273
What answers me is an even more scorching kiss. My heartbeat remains restless and shaky.

477
00:31:41,273 --> 00:31:51,266
Lucien: Yes… I won’t give myself another chance to lose you.

478
00:31:51,468 --> 00:31:53,831
*: "走马灯" (zǒu mǎ dēng) refers to a spinning lantern with paper horses. Metaphorically, it describes fleeting, dreamlike scenes, often used for life flashing before one’s eyes.

479
00:31:53,831 --> 00:31:56,667
**: "神经衰弱" (shén jīng shuāi ruò) translates to "neurasthenia" or "weak nerves." While rare in the West, it's still recognized in some Asian countries as a persistent mental disorder with symptoms like weakness, emotional instability, tension-induced pain, and sleep disturbances caused by ‘weak nerves’.

480
00:31:56,667 --> 00:31:59,368
*** His eyes are described with three words: 晦暗 (huì àn), 疯狂 (fēng kuáng), 深切 (shēn qiè).
-晦暗: Shadowed and obscure, as if hiding intense emotions.
-疯狂: A chaotic, unrestrained madness, unlike his usual controlled obsession (偏执 piān zhí).

481
00:31:59,368 --> 00:32:01,461
深切 (shēn qiè) combines "深" (deep) and "切" (cut/slice), usually used to convey the most sincere emotions. The way I interpret it is that his profound, raw emotions and vulnerabilities are fully exposed, like his heart being laid bare after getting cut open.

482
00:32:01,900 --> 00:32:05,377
3:00 AM.

483
00:32:05,377 --> 00:32:10,982
Monochrome liquid flows through a blood-collecting device into the vacuum tube as Lucien slightly loosens his tightly clenched fingers.

484
00:32:10,982 --> 00:32:17,194
High-speed metal instruments hum without pause while the surrounding screens flash with streams of data—shifting graphs and numbers reflected in pairs of focused and urgent eyes.

485
00:32:17,194 --> 00:32:21,346
Lucien shifts his gaze to the clock on the wall and speaks in a cold voice.

486
00:32:21,346 --> 00:32:26,714
Lucien: We still need to make up eight hours.

487
00:32:26,714 --> 00:32:34,445
After speaking, he tosses the cotton swab used to press against his vein into the trash. He removes his clothes and, assisted by the researchers, puts on monitoring equipment and a respirator before lying down in the experimental chamber.

488
00:32:34,445 --> 00:32:40,319
According to his calculations, the data samples were originally expected to reach No. 58 today, leaving at most 39 hours until the No. 63 that he needed.

489
00:32:40,319 --> 00:32:48,017
But an accident still happened. In his anxiety, he used space folding to bring the girl back to his room from the ruins.

490
00:32:48,017 --> 00:32:53,114
Rationality told him he shouldn’t have done it. But he was desperate to confirm her real existence, to wash away the dirt and wounds that had tainted her.

491
00:32:53,114 --> 00:32:59,563
Or rather, he had truly felt a certain fear, one that made it impossible for him to calmly leave her in any situation where another accident could occur.

492
00:32:59,563 --> 00:33:06,855
However, the price was that the Evol fluctuations affected the experimental environment, briefly stalling the data progress.

493
00:33:06,855 --> 00:33:13,168
Even the slightest deviation is something Lucien refuses to accept.

494
00:33:13,168 --> 00:33:18,401
If the purpose of accelerating his pace before was to safely obtain the special sample and return to her as soon as possible…

495
00:33:18,401 --> 00:33:23,060
…then now, he has an even stronger reason to race against time.

496
00:33:23,060 --> 00:33:30,791
Lucien: If any abnormal fluctuations occur during the process, as long as the values don’t reach their peak, there’s no need to pause.

497
00:33:30,791 --> 00:33:35,247
Lucien: Begin the experiment.

498
00:33:35,247 --> 00:33:40,818
Lucien closes his eyes, letting the liquid engulf him.

499
00:33:40,818 --> 00:33:47,029
In a trance, the complicated emotions from moments ago rise even faster than the water, suddenly making it hard for him to breathe.

500
00:33:47,029 --> 00:33:53,646
The moment he realized he hadn’t received a message from her reporting her safety, the moment he saw that her flight had lost communication on trending—

501
00:33:53,646 --> 00:33:58,981
—only then did he discover that a heart could contract this severely in an instant.

502
00:33:58,981 --> 00:34:04,652
The stabbing pain in his chest spread along his nerves, making him instinctively furrow his brows and inexplicably take a step forward.

503
00:34:04,652 --> 00:34:10,223
He didn’t know where he was going, nor did he even know why he was moving forward.

504
00:34:10,223 --> 00:34:15,996
Perhaps he just didn't want to stay in place, or perhaps it was just a subconscious reflex of self-deception.

505
00:34:15,996 --> 00:34:21,836
Broken pavement carried the lingering charred scent, and severed electrical wires hung down, scraping eerie marks onto the ground.

506
00:34:21,836 --> 00:34:26,563
The world remained as monotonous and colorless as ever, as if this had always been its true color.

507
00:34:26,563 --> 00:34:31,795
After walking aimlessly past several street corners, a streak of bright color crashed into his vision without warning.

508
00:34:31,795 --> 00:34:36,218
She appeared so abruptly, like a grand hallucination, catching him completely off guard.

509
00:34:36,218 --> 00:34:41,586
Lucien instinctively stopped in his tracks.

510
00:34:41,586 --> 00:34:48,068
Suddenly, he recalled a moment from long ago. Beneath the camphor tree in early spring, he had seen that streak of a phantom that seemed almost real.

511
00:34:48,068 --> 00:34:55,833
Lucien: [gasps] ….

512
00:34:55,833 --> 00:35:02,011
Lucien: It shouldn’t be like this.

513
00:35:02,011 --> 00:35:09,236
Even though reason told him that there were countless possibilities that she wouldn't be here, an unreasonable certainty drove Lucien towards his only color.

514
00:35:10,653 --> 00:35:14,772
Somewhat distant sounds from the equipment scratch at his eardrums, and Lucien knows that the experiment is going smoothly.

515
00:35:14,772 --> 00:35:21,018
It seems he can return to her side soon.

516
00:35:21,018 --> 00:35:27,297
Not much time has passed. She probably won’t notice anything.

517
00:35:27,297 --> 00:35:32,192
But she has always been sharper than he thought. If she picks up on something, what then?

518
00:35:32,192 --> 00:35:37,324
In truth, he dislikes this kind of wavering irresolution and, even more so, the feeling of losing control to accidents.

519
00:35:37,324 --> 00:35:41,882
Accidents are supposed to be challenges and abundant possibilities, not something that leaves him helpless and in a flustered mess like this.

520
00:35:41,882 --> 00:35:47,722
But to ensure the experiment goes smoothly, he has no choice but to accelerate the process. This means he cannot be by her side all the time.

521
00:35:47,722 --> 00:35:52,347
So, he chose the safest method at this stage.

522
00:35:52,347 --> 00:35:57,344
Before leaving his room, he locked her inside a dream.

523
00:35:57,681 --> 00:36:02,678
*: SOBBING at the every Out of Plan R&S/S1 Chapter 25 reference—I did not need to be reminded of his hallucination of her after her death every five seconds!! 😭 Also, oh my god, the constant mentions of his colorblindness and how she's the only color in his world… PG really loves twisting the knife for us XM stans huh😭💔

524
00:36:03,421 --> 00:36:07,776
Sure enough, by the next night, Lucien pushes open the door of his room and walks in, calmly picking up the duffel bag he had packed at noon.

525
00:36:07,776 --> 00:36:10,510
Lucien: MC, we should go.

526
00:36:10,510 --> 00:36:12,333
MC: ...Go home? So soon?

527
00:36:12,333 --> 00:36:18,748
Lucien: Yes, but... there might be some complications along the way.

528
00:36:18,748 --> 00:36:21,651
As he speaks, the air outside hums loudly, as if the aftershocks of distant artillery fire continuously ripple through the atmosphere.

529
00:36:21,651 --> 00:36:24,352
Meanwhile, this trembling persisted for almost the entire afternoon, making me slightly uneasy.

530
00:36:24,352 --> 00:36:28,201
Lucien: MC, although I know this is putting you in a bit of a tough spot...

531
00:36:28,201 --> 00:36:35,324
Lucien: But the only way we can evacuate now is by helicopter.

532
00:36:35,324 --> 00:36:36,573
MC: …!

533
00:36:36,573 --> 00:36:38,430
My body nearly trembles on instinct.

534
00:36:38,430 --> 00:36:40,962
But Lucien reacts even faster. He wraps an arm around my waist, his long, narrow eyes gazing deeply at me.

535
00:36:40,962 --> 00:36:44,000
Lucien: I don’t want to make you afraid.

536
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:50,179
Lucien: If there were any better solution, I would never allow something like this to happen.

537
00:36:50,179 --> 00:36:52,474
As he speaks, he holds out his palm toward me. On it lies a single white pill.

538
00:36:52,474 --> 00:36:54,939
Lucien: MC, do you trust me?

539
00:36:54,939 --> 00:37:05,337
Lucien: This is a sedative, and it has a safe composition. When you wake up, the first thing you see will be a safer place.

540
00:37:05,337 --> 00:37:12,393
Boom—!

541
00:37:12,393 --> 00:37:15,296
An even more intense blast slams through layers of air. This time, even the floor beneath my feet begins to shake faintly.

542
00:37:15,296 --> 00:37:17,761
Looking into those unwavering eyes, I take a deep breath then pick up the pill and the water bottle.

543
00:37:17,761 --> 00:37:19,482
MC: Have you got what you wanted?

544
00:37:19,482 --> 00:37:22,622
Seemingly not expecting that I still have the mind to care about this matter, he freezes briefly, then his eyes crinkle into a smile.

545
00:37:22,622 --> 00:37:26,437
Lucien: Of course, I never break my word.

546
00:37:26,437 --> 00:37:28,935
MC: So, the state I’ll be in after taking it is also within your calculations, right?

547
00:37:28,935 --> 00:37:36,936
Lucien: Yes. Don’t worry, I’ll handle everything.

548
00:37:36,936 --> 00:37:38,827
I feel relieved and swallow the white pill in one gulp.

549
00:37:38,827 --> 00:37:41,967
In my dazed state, I suddenly feel a violent tremor—

550
00:37:41,967 --> 00:37:49,056
At the same time, bursts of explosions ring out one after another, near and far. It’s as if the entire world is roaring, clamoring to rush toward me.

551
00:37:49,056 --> 00:37:50,339
MC: …Ah!

552
00:37:51,656 --> 00:37:53,783
I abruptly open my eyes, but my consciousness stays foggy, feeling nothing but the world spinning around me.

553
00:37:53,783 --> 00:37:56,585
Until my vision slowly comes into focus, and I suddenly meet a pair of startled, slightly panicked eyes. My mind blanks out in an instant.

554
00:37:58,138 --> 00:38:00,636
Lucien sits across from me, his face pale. Fresh blood seeps through his tattered shirt, snaking down his body in rivulets.

555
00:38:00,636 --> 00:38:04,080
Each blast of distant artillery fire is carried by the raging wind, thrashing wildly inside the aircraft cabin. In the almost suffocating air pressure, my entire body trembles uncontrollably.

556
00:38:04,080 --> 00:38:05,464
MC: Lucien!

557
00:38:05,464 --> 00:38:08,165
I shout at him, my voice choked as all the unease and pain in my heart burst out at once.

558
00:38:08,165 --> 00:38:11,676
His dark pupils shrink for a split second, but he immediately smiles reassuringly at me. He reaches out his hand toward me as if wanting to caress my cheek.

559
00:38:11,676 --> 00:38:14,478
Brownish blood seeps from the bandaged wound on that well-defined hand, mingled with tiny grains of sand and grit.

560
00:38:14,478 --> 00:38:18,124
Everything happens too suddenly. I stare blankly at the IV tube secured to his arm. As it sways and tugs, I catch a glimpse of faint bloodstains around the needle site on his hand.

561
00:38:18,124 --> 00:38:21,466
Lucien: MC, I'm fine.

562
00:38:21,466 --> 00:38:25,078
Lucien: Close your eyes...

563
00:38:25,078 --> 00:38:27,442
The howling wind and rain instantly swallow up his voice. I bite my lip hard, fighting to push words through

564
00:38:27,442 --> 00:38:30,851
However, the helicopter suddenly tilts sharply to one side. I instinctively grip my seatbelt tightly, but the intense pulling force nearly overwhelms my shoulders and back.

565
00:38:30,851 --> 00:38:33,113
Every bone in my body feels as if being torn apart, and my brain seems vacuumed of air.

566
00:38:33,113 --> 00:38:35,477
My entire body is deathly stiff in my seat, only my heart pounding violently in my chest.

567
00:38:35,477 --> 00:38:37,232
I can't help but shout at Lucien in front of me.

568
00:38:37,232 --> 00:38:38,988
MC: Lucien! You Big Liar!!!

569
00:38:38,988 --> 00:38:41,790
The person across from me freezes for a moment, as if struck by a sudden thought, then immediately shows a faint, particularly conceding smile.

570
00:38:41,790 --> 00:38:48,305
Lucien: Yes, I'm a big liar. It's all my fault.

571
00:38:48,305 --> 00:38:50,702
MC: You even said it was all within your calculations. Was your injury part of that too?!

572
00:38:50,702 --> 00:39:00,257
Lucien: I don’t mean to upset you on purpose, but none of these are serious wounds, so yes, they fall within my calculations.

573
00:39:00,257 --> 00:39:02,113
MC: ...Y-you, stop talking! Don’t make me mad!

574
00:39:02,113 --> 00:39:07,515
Lucien: Then just be angry. As long as you’re only mad at me, that’s fine.

575
00:39:07,515 --> 00:39:09,034
MC: You bad guy!!

576
00:39:10,115 --> 00:39:12,883
As he unintentionally or intentionally fans the flames, those crushing fears are unknowingly pushed out by anger.

577
00:39:14,233 --> 00:39:16,428
By the time I regain my senses, I realize we’ve come to a stop on the deck of a cargo ship—

578
00:39:16,428 --> 00:39:18,757
A foreign man stands not far away, greeting us with a friendly smile.

579
00:39:20,141 --> 00:39:22,640
The cabin's guest room isn’t large, but it has all the essentials. Devoted medical personnel even come in to treat Lucien’s wounds.

580
00:39:22,640 --> 00:39:25,307
Until they leave with the medical kit, I continue to stand not far away, watching him with a pained heart and furrowing my brows.

581
00:39:25,307 --> 00:39:27,130
MC: Does it hurt?

582
00:39:27,130 --> 00:39:29,797
Lucien: Are you still afraid?

583
00:39:29,797 --> 00:39:32,633
The words we speak come out simultaneously, causing us to freeze in the same instant and then share a tacit smile.

584
00:39:32,633 --> 00:39:39,722
Lucien: Hurts a lot, so come hug me, okay?

585
00:39:39,722 --> 00:39:41,478
He knows I can never do anything about him.

586
00:39:41,478 --> 00:39:44,584
I walk up to him, and he wraps his arms around my waist. His fluffy head leans against my chest, and for a moment, it feels like the tension melts away.

587
00:39:44,584 --> 00:39:46,305
MC: …So now you realize you still have me.

588
00:39:46,305 --> 00:39:54,813
Lucien: I can’t do it alone, after all. But I can’t always rely on you either.

589
00:39:54,813 --> 00:39:59,911
Lucien: Even though I really want to.

590
00:39:59,911 --> 00:40:02,105
Hearing the slightly aggrieved tone in his voice, I feel both exasperated and amused.

591
00:40:02,105 --> 00:40:04,435
MC: If I had stayed asleep, were you planning to hide your injuries?

592
00:40:04,435 --> 00:40:11,963
Lucien: Maybe. I'm sorry, MC.

593
00:40:11,963 --> 00:40:13,786
MC: You big fool, it’s not like I’m blaming you for getting hurt.

594
00:40:13,786 --> 00:40:20,775
Lucien: I know. I’m just really sorry for making you wake up early.

595
00:40:20,775 --> 00:40:27,763
Lucien: The dosage of the sedative was precisely calculated by me. You were supposed to wake up only after we landed.

596
00:40:27,763 --> 00:40:35,292
Lucien: But… we encountered an unexpected attack during the retreat, which delayed us for a bit.

597
00:40:35,292 --> 00:40:37,587
He explains with excessive seriousness and caution, making my heart ache faintly.

598
00:40:37,587 --> 00:40:39,647
While I've suffered trauma, he seems to have been wounded as well.

599
00:40:39,647 --> 00:40:42,516
Those wounds are hidden in corners I can’t see, leaving me with nothing to do but press silent kisses onto his calm face, one after another.

600
00:40:42,516 --> 00:40:45,116
Remembering the foreign man on the deck earlier, I can’t help but gently stroke his brows with some concern.

601
00:40:45,116 --> 00:40:47,580
MC: Lucien, can we really trust these people and make it back to Loveland City without any problems?

602
00:40:47,580 --> 00:40:54,704
Lucien: When the helicopter landed, I noticed the Holden Institute’s insignia on the ship’s stern.

603
00:40:54,704 --> 00:41:02,840
Lucien: On the path from the deck to the guest rooms, a section of the wooden floorboards makes a subtly different sound when stepped on compared to the rest.

604
00:41:02,840 --> 00:41:09,052
Lucien: It is highly possible that he used such a design to transport things he didn't want others to discover easily.

605
00:41:09,052 --> 00:41:16,513
Lucien: Moreover, a considerable amount of this institute's funding comes from underground deals that can’t see the light of day.

606
00:41:16,513 --> 00:41:29,409
Lucien: So I deduce that Holden uses this ship to transport collectibles for trade. Of course, the possibility of smuggling weapons can’t be ruled out either.

607
00:41:29,409 --> 00:41:32,076
Lucien seems to notice my nervousness and gently places his palm on the back of my hand.

608
00:41:32,076 --> 00:41:39,638
Lucien: More importantly, after the helicopter landed, I discovered an Evol-suppressing device that’s difficult to detect.

609
00:41:39,638 --> 00:41:47,268
Lucien: Based on my past observations in the lab, I think there’s a high probability that this ship also carries research samples.

610
00:41:47,268 --> 00:41:49,631
MC: ...Could it be that they also made an emergency transfer while evacuating?

611
00:41:49,631 --> 00:41:56,046
Lucien: We can’t be certain yet, but I think they must’ve set quite a few backup plans in place.

612
00:41:56,046 --> 00:41:57,970
MC: …Will what they're doing affect your objectives?

613
00:41:57,970 --> 00:42:03,136
Lucien: It will have some impact, but it doesn’t matter.

614
00:42:03,136 --> 00:42:10,225
Lucien: I won’t give them the chance. I’ll either find the item or no one will.*

615
00:42:10,225 --> 00:42:12,521
Hearing him say that, I can’t help but feel a little worried and instinctively hold his hand.

616
00:42:12,521 --> 00:42:14,344
MC: Let me help you too, okay?

617
00:42:14,344 --> 00:42:18,024
Lucien: Of course I need your help.

618
00:42:18,024 --> 00:42:28,523
Lucien: I need you to keep staying well by my side and embracing me just like this.

619
00:42:28,523 --> 00:42:31,427
His gentle whispers brush past my fingertips, but I feel a silent rejection and purse my lips a bit unhappily.

620
00:42:31,427 --> 00:42:33,047
MC: Are you still afraid?

621
00:42:33,047 --> 00:42:35,343
MC: Because of what happened before, you just want to put me in the safest place.

622
00:42:35,343 --> 00:42:37,267
He doesn’t speak, as if this is yet another form of silent acknowledgment.

623
00:42:37,267 --> 00:42:40,711
Relief and dread are intertwined. I’ve known for a long time that he buries his emotions even deeper than I do, which is why I need to embrace him tighter and for longer.

624
00:42:40,711 --> 00:42:43,006
MC: I admit that the airplane incident scared me out of my mind, and even now, I’m still shaking.

625
00:42:43,006 --> 00:42:45,673
MC: But I'm also worried that you'll be in danger, though I trust you, believe you can accomplish anything...

626
00:42:45,673 --> 00:42:47,564
MC: Lucien, I want you safely by my side too.

627
00:42:47,564 --> 00:42:50,704
His profound eyes are filled with my reflection. He simply gazes at me for a long time, as if this way he could lock me within them forever.

628
00:42:50,704 --> 00:42:53,573
In the end, Lucien only tilts his head up and kisses me even deeper.

629
00:42:53,607 --> 00:42:55,734
*: The literal tl is “I will either find the item or take care of/dispose of (it/him/them).” I decided to take some artistic liberties to capture this vagueness. The phrase "处理掉" (chǔ lǐ diào) is often used when something is taken care of through destruction, removal, or getting rid of something. It could mean he’s simply going to dispose of the item or eliminate the people involved or… both-

630
00:42:55,734 --> 00:42:58,367
Inside the cabin, the banquet hall emanates a touch of warmth that feels out of place.

631
00:42:58,367 --> 00:43:01,338
The flowing lights fall upon Lucien’s black shirt, where the glimpses of bandages beneath inexplicably add some bewitching allure to his elegant demeanor.

632
00:43:01,338 --> 00:43:04,444
Early in the morning, Holden selects several formal dresses and sends them over, saying that since today is New Year’s Eve in Loveland City, everyone should start adapting to local customs.

633
00:43:04,444 --> 00:43:07,415
I can’t shake the feeling that he has ulterior motives. Just as I lean in to whisper to Lucien, I see Holden raising his glass and approaching us.

634
00:43:07,415 --> 00:43:10,521
Holden: Thanks to Professor Lucien’s involvement, our experiment has achieved substantial progress.

635
00:43:10,521 --> 00:43:13,593
Holden: Although the process has been filled with too many unforeseen 'uncertainties', forcing us to start over from the beginning, I believe it has all been worth it.

636
00:43:13,593 --> 00:43:16,395
Holden: Just as you said, accidents are to be enjoyed.

637
00:43:16,395 --> 00:43:19,265
Holden: I trust that after returning to Loveland City, we’ll be able to collaborate more deeply, don’t you agree?

638
00:43:19,265 --> 00:43:23,552
Lucien: I've always enjoyed working with intelligent people.

639
00:43:23,552 --> 00:43:27,570
Beneath the calm of this moment, something continues to surge in the undercurrents.

640
00:43:27,570 --> 00:43:30,439
Aside from Lucien and me, nearly everyone on the ship belongs to Holden’s team.

641
00:43:30,439 --> 00:43:34,659
If Lucien wants to find what he’s looking for without using Evol, these past few days have shown that it won’t be an easy task.

642
00:43:34,659 --> 00:43:38,474
Silently, I lift my gaze toward Lucien. His expression remains composed, as if unconcerned by the present circumstances.

643
00:43:38,474 --> 00:43:47,893
Lucien: Speaking of which, that matter I previously requested you to arrange...

644
00:43:47,893 --> 00:43:53,329
Holden: Of course, no problem.

645
00:43:53,329 --> 00:43:57,481
The other person raises an eyebrow. Soon, this simple banquet comes to a close.

646
00:43:58,427 --> 00:44:02,377
But Lucien does not take me back to the room. Instead, he weaves left and right before finally arriving at the cargo ship’s kitchen.

647
00:44:02,377 --> 00:44:06,259
I blink in confusion, then turn to him with a laugh.

648
00:44:06,259 --> 00:44:10,040
MC: Professor Lucien, didn’t you eat your fill?

649
00:44:10,040 --> 00:44:15,104
Lucien: I really didn’t have much of an appetite in that atmosphere.

650
00:44:15,104 --> 00:44:23,409
Lucien: But more than that, I just want to share a simple meal with you alone today.

651
00:44:23,409 --> 00:44:27,022
As he speaks, he opens the freezer door and unexpectedly takes out several bags of frozen dumplings.

652
00:44:27,022 --> 00:44:29,992
MC: There are actually dumplings here…!

653
00:44:29,992 --> 00:44:34,381
As I recall that the banquet mainly featured Western dishes, I vaguely understand the cryptic exchange Lucien and the other party were trading earlier.

654
00:44:34,381 --> 00:44:41,505
Lucien: Apologies. I originally planned to show you my cooking skills at home this year.

655
00:44:41,505 --> 00:44:50,012
Lucien: But now, it seems we’ll have to wait until we’re back for my Great Producer to properly appraise it.

656
00:44:50,012 --> 00:44:53,354
MC: No need to apologize. After all, we're still spending this Chinese New Year's Eve together.

657
00:44:53,354 --> 00:44:56,967
MC: But Professor Lucien, you better not forget the New Year’s Eve dinner you owe me~

658
00:44:56,967 --> 00:45:00,377
As we chat and laugh, we set the pot to boil, and before long, billowing steam fills our surroundings.

659
00:45:00,377 --> 00:45:04,462
The cold, stiff dumplings tumble into the pot. As I watch the tiny bubbles on the water’s surface, I suddenly feel that this moment is very peaceful.

660
00:45:04,462 --> 00:45:08,277
For a fleeting instant, it feels as if we’ve returned to our warm home.

661
00:45:08,277 --> 00:45:11,923
Lucien: MC, Happy New Year.

662
00:45:11,923 --> 00:45:16,008
Hearing the blessing that falls by my ear, I turn my head and find the answer in those smiling eyes.

663
00:45:16,008 --> 00:45:26,271
Lucien: I think, the more we're in this kind of atmosphere, the more we need some relaxation.

664
00:45:26,271 --> 00:45:28,364
He lifts the lid and serves a bowl of dumplings.

665
00:45:28,364 --> 00:45:31,132
The steaming mist blurs his eyes, making it hard to see them clearly.

666
00:45:31,132 --> 00:45:34,339
He picks up a dumpling, brings it to his lips to blow on it carefully, and then holds it to my mouth.

667
00:45:34,339 --> 00:45:37,952
Although its skin is a bit tough and the filling is rather ordinary, the steaming dumpling still brings me a sense of happiness as it enters my mouth.

668
00:45:37,952 --> 00:45:42,104
Afterward, I can’t help but pick up one for him as well. We share the meal in silence, as though words aren’t needed.

669
00:45:42,104 --> 00:45:46,797
MC: It’s incredible. Though everything’s been coincidental and absurd, spending New Year’s here with you doesn’t feel wrong at all.

670
00:45:46,797 --> 00:45:52,637
Lucien:  Silly girl.

671
00:45:52,637 --> 00:45:56,115
In the dense steam, he leans in close to my lips.

672
00:45:56,115 --> 00:46:01,044
Softer than his lips, his tongue lingers even longer, not just bringing happiness but planting a seed that blooms endlessly in my heart.

673
00:46:01,044 --> 00:46:10,564
Lucien: It will be over soon. After that, we’ll leave immediately.

674
00:46:10,564 --> 00:46:14,919
His words sound like some kind of farewell, making me subconsciously worried.

675
00:46:14,919 --> 00:46:18,599
But before I can ask, a wave of inexplicable dizziness comes over me-

676
00:46:18,599 --> 00:46:24,372
I struggle to keep my eyes open, but Lucien's face gradually dissolves into the darkness.

677
00:46:24,372 --> 00:46:29,976
Gazing at the girl asleep in his arms, Lucien kisses her on the forehead once more.

678
00:46:29,976 --> 00:46:35,479
Holding her quietly, he carries her back to the guest room, lays her on the bed, and carefully tucks her in.

679
00:46:35,479 --> 00:46:41,758
Lucien: Sweet dreams, MC.

680
00:46:41,758 --> 00:46:46,181
When he turns around again, the tenderness on his face has already vanished. His narrow eyes glint with icy coldness.

681
00:46:46,181 --> 00:46:52,022
Just as planned, he smoothly enters the concealed storage room he had noticed earlier. Based on his analysis over the past few days, he also located the reagent he wanted to verify.

682
00:46:52,022 --> 00:46:55,296
As expected, it has lost its activity.

683
00:46:55,296 --> 00:47:00,867
Though this isn’t a good outcome, when weighed against the girl’s safety, it can hardly be considered an excessive loss.

684
00:47:00,867 --> 00:47:04,715
It can be considered that everything has gone as he wished.

685
00:47:04,715 --> 00:47:08,834
He casually finds a spot to sit and speaks calmly.

686
00:47:08,834 --> 00:47:16,869
Lucien: Professor Holden, you still won't come out. Aren’t you afraid I’ll destroy this thing?

687
00:47:18,557 --> 00:47:23,486
In a drowsy haze, I open my eyes.

688
00:47:23,486 --> 00:47:30,947
The room is dark and almost lightless, lit only by faint moonlight filtering through the porthole. There’s no Lucien by my side.

689
00:47:30,947 --> 00:47:34,863
Surrounded by deathly silence, I suddenly have a terrible feeling. I grab Lucien’s coat and drape it over my shoulders without much thought before leaving the room.

690
00:47:34,863 --> 00:47:39,455
The quiet corridor seems endless—it's as if I'm trapped again.

691
00:47:39,455 --> 00:47:44,215
At this moment, my mind is surprisingly calm. Those pair of serene yet inscrutable eyes flash through my thoughts.

692
00:47:44,215 --> 00:47:47,523
Perhaps… I finally grasp why all of this is happening.

693
00:47:47,523 --> 00:47:51,440
...Lucien, you truly are an absolute big fool, a big bad guy!

694
00:47:51,440 --> 00:47:55,052
In an instant, a familiar force surges from my chest, and a lustrous white light burst forth—

695
00:47:55,052 --> 00:47:57,651
I need to have a proper talk with Lucien.

696
00:47:57,651 --> 00:48:01,264
A bone-chilling cold permeates the air, making it feel like even one's breath could freeze into a thin layer of ice.

697
00:48:01,264 --> 00:48:05,349
Crystal-clear ice spreads throughout the corridor of the cabin. Icicles hang from the ceiling here and there, their tips sharp as blades.

698
00:48:05,349 --> 00:48:09,906
Scattered weapons and unknown equipment lie strewn everywhere. I stare blankly at this frost-covered scene as countless terrifying images seem to flash before my eyes.

699
00:48:09,906 --> 00:48:14,565
Without another thought, I pick up a dropped handgun and sprint toward the frozen corridor’s end.

700
00:48:14,565 --> 00:48:18,819
There is no sign of anyone on the ship, deathly silent as if it had been swept clean, with traces of frost all over the place.

701
00:48:18,819 --> 00:48:22,972
I don’t know how long I’ve been running until I stop in front of an unremarkable door—

702
00:48:22,972 --> 00:48:27,867
the only door that hasn’t been frozen shut.

703
00:48:27,867 --> 00:48:32,222
I cautiously look around, then gently push the door so that it opens a crack.

704
00:48:32,222 --> 00:48:37,522
Various artworks are scattered throughout the small space, while cold light falls indifferently, making the entire room feel even more cramped and somber.

705
00:48:37,522 --> 00:48:43,025
Under the cold light in the corner, numerous packaged artworks haphazardly piled on the floor, like a small exhibition yet to be unveiled.

706
00:48:43,025 --> 00:48:47,245
Strips of bright yellow tape cut a glaring boundary across my vision, warning away any visitors who don’t belong there.

707
00:48:47,245 --> 00:48:51,938
A cold, indifferent figure stands at the center. He turns as if sensing something, and his gaze crashes into my furrowed eyes.

708
00:48:51,938 --> 00:48:55,989
The air falls into silence.

709
00:48:55,989 --> 00:49:01,931
Everything before me seems beyond ‘excuse’. His calm gaze dips slightly, eyelashes casting a faint shadow over his tranquil face.

710
00:49:01,931 --> 00:49:07,197
Like a bad kid who knows he's doing something wrong but still insists on doing it, soberly indulges in his own actions.

711
00:49:07,197 --> 00:49:13,004
I walk step by step toward him, check that he has no additional wounds, and only then do I turn my gaze to him.

712
00:49:13,004 --> 00:49:16,211
MC: Is there anything you want to say to me?

713
00:49:16,211 --> 00:49:18,777
Lucien: ….

714
00:49:18,777 --> 00:49:22,356
He blinks and smiles, his expression somewhere between resignation and satisfaction.

715
00:49:22,356 --> 00:49:27,386
Lucien: [that mix of helplessness and pride at her managing to break out the dream using her power:"] Your power has grown stronger.

716
00:49:27,386 --> 00:49:31,741
A rush of heat relentlessly floods upward and I can’t help but tremble all over. I scan the room and then point to a table covered with bubble wrap.

717
00:49:31,741 --> 00:49:34,948
MC: Lie down.

718
00:49:34,948 --> 00:49:38,662
Lucien: ….

719
00:49:38,662 --> 00:49:44,334
Maybe my tone is too harsh, or I seem on the verge of anger, Lucien says nothing and simply lies down quietly.

720
00:49:44,334 --> 00:49:48,554
Then, I forcefully rip off the yellow tape nearby and walk back to his side.

721
00:49:48,554 --> 00:49:51,963
MC: Put your hands behind your back.

722
00:49:51,963 --> 00:49:56,420
As if it were some tacitly understood command, he obeys me without a word.

723
00:49:56,420 --> 00:50:02,227
I resentfully wind the tape around his body, but out of the corner of my eye, I catch the faint bloodstains seeping through, and the strength of my hands falters with reluctance.

724
00:50:02,227 --> 00:50:08,168
Eventually, the tape coils loosely around his neck, shoulders, arms, and down to his exposed abdomen. It’s as if he, too, were a dangerous yet precious collectible.

725
00:50:08,168 --> 00:50:13,435
Lucien continues to let me do as I please. As the tape adheres to his skin, his expression shifts, initially calm and quiet but now touched with enigmatic depth and curiosity.

726
00:50:13,435 --> 00:50:18,938
He watches my every move without blinking. Clearly, he's the one who's bound, yet it feels as if I'm the subject of his interest.

727
00:50:18,938 --> 00:50:24,103
The inexplicable impulse melts into guilt. Suddenly, I catch sight of a golf club nearby and, feigning composure, pick it up.

728
00:50:25,757 --> 00:50:27,817
MC: Lucien, do you know what I’m doing?

729
00:50:27,817 --> 00:50:30,383
Lucien: I know.

730
00:50:30,383 --> 00:50:35,615
Lucien: But just doing this... I’m afraid it’s not quite enough.

731
00:50:35,615 --> 00:50:38,282
As he speaks, he lifts a hand that had somehow slipped free at some point and rests it against the back of my head.

732
00:50:38,282 --> 00:50:41,625
His slender fingers slide into my hair, stroking through the strands. Every so often, his fingertips lightly graze the curve of my ear, sending a faint, tremulous weakness through my body.

733
00:50:41,625 --> 00:50:44,967
Just as I teeter on the edge of surrender, he leans in, closing the distance between us. His lips trail up along my cheek before gently biting down on my earlobe.

734
00:50:44,967 --> 00:50:51,685
Lucien: It needs to be this much, at least.

735
00:50:51,685 --> 00:50:55,298
The bubble wrap around us rustles from friction as I press my bent knee against the inside of his thigh, but afraid of hurting him, I instinctively ease the pressure.

736
00:50:55,298 --> 00:50:57,323
Yet the man beneath me doesn’t seem satisfied with my movement.

737
00:50:57,323 --> 00:51:01,104
He wickedly shifts his leg, making me suddenly lose my fulcrum and involuntarily tip forward, but he swiftly tightens his hold on me with his thighs, leaving me to almost completely surrender my balance to him.

738
00:51:01,104 --> 00:51:02,455
MC: You…

739
00:51:02,455 --> 00:51:05,898
Lucien: There’s no one else here.

740
00:51:05,898 --> 00:51:18,423
